  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Archdiocese of Lilongwe Integrated HIV and AIDS Programme-Mchinji Deanery</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Working in targeted communities in 5 parishes in Lilongwe Archdiocese, the project aims to: reduce the spread of HIV infection; provide access to treatment for people living with HIV and AIDS; mitigate the health, socio-economic and psychosocial impact of HIV and AIDS on individuals, families and communities, especially women and vulnerable children; and mobilise the community on issues of water, hygiene and sanitation.

It will do this through: training young people on HIV awareness and sensitisation and life skills, and providing support through youth clubs and activities; training experts and volunteers on services and support for PLWHA and OVCs; training communities in water and sanitation issues, and facilitating the establishment of water and sanitation committees and support structures; and strengthening the communities&#x2019; capacity to implement and manage these programmes. 

The project will build on existing diocesan programmes and structures, in collaboration with other stakeholders such as government, NGOs, FBOs and donor partners.</narrative>
  </description>
